Package Ensemble

Interface Ensemble<T>

Type Parameters:
T - the type of the elements of the set
All Known Implementing Classes:
MathsEnsemble
public interface Ensemble<T>
This interface represents a mathematical set of objects. It is used to represent a set of objects.

    • contient

      boolean contient(T element)
      This method checks if the set contains a given element, true if it does, false otherwise.
      Parameters:
      element - the element to check
      Returns:
      true if the set contains the element, false otherwise

    • union

      Ensemble<T> union(Ensemble<T> autre)
      This method returns the union of the set with another set. It creates a new set that contains all the elements of both sets.
      Parameters:
      autre - the other set to union with
      Returns:
      the union of the two sets

    • intersection

      Ensemble<T> intersection(Ensemble<T> autre)
      This method returns the intersection of the set with another set. It creates a new set that contains only the elements that are in both sets.
      Parameters:
      autre - the other set to intersect with
      Returns:
      the intersection of the two sets

    • difference

      Ensemble<T> difference(Ensemble<T> autre)
      This method returns the difference of the set with another set. It creates a new set that contains only the elements that are in this set but not in the other set.
      Parameters:
      autre - the other set to difference with
      Returns:
      the difference of the two sets

    • diffSymetrique

      Ensemble<T> diffSymetrique(Ensemble<T> autre)
      This method returns the symmetric difference of the set with another set. It creates a new set that contains only the elements that are in either set but not in both.
      Parameters:
      autre - the other set to symmetric difference with
      Returns:
      the symmetric difference of the two sets

    • produitCartesien

      Ensemble<Couple<T>> produitCartesien(Ensemble<T> autre)
      This method returns the Cartesian product of the set with another set. It creates a new set that contains all the pairs of elements from both sets.
      Parameters:
      autre - the other set to product with
      Returns:
      the Cartesian product of the two sets
